The Golden Age started somewhat before that, but I'm able actually to bring, even though I'm starting in 1911, I'll have Morgan and Huntington and Folger and Widener and Rosenbach, all of this place, you know, at the current auction.

20:38.656 --> 20:39.598
The whole auction.

20:39.618 --> 20:40.359
The whole auction.

20:40.379 --> 20:41.542
The whole auction.

20:41.562 --> 20:43.646
That's really when Huntington became known.

20:43.666 --> 20:46.912
He really wasn't known as a collector until then.

20:46.932 --> 20:58.915
And those books by Leslie Morris, the two Rosenbach's exhibition, I just realized that, I mean, Rosenbach couldn't have existed without Huntington.

20:59.136 --> 20:59.196
No.

